The paper focuses on learning robot objective functions from human input during task execution, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses state-of-the-art techniques in machine learning (cs.AI) and proposes a new method for learning conservatively (cs.LG). The experiment involves human interaction data and a user study, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of unintended learning, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
